Meriam Berka

Bio

hello! My name is Meriam, Im a second year MHS student in Epidemiology at the John Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health. Im a social epidemiologist whos interested in maternal and womens health, my background is in sociology so Im very interested in structural analyses of the causes of health inequity. Im also a research assistant for the Center for Indigenous Health where I primarily use STATA for data cleaning and analysis work. Ive tried to make the switch to R quite a few times on my own but intro R courses have been my Sisyphus boulder, the accountability and guidance of this class was a major motivation to take it.

Some facts about me

1. Im Moroccan! And a born Baltimorean but I grew up in Calgary, AB near the Rockies.

2. Im a big hobbies person. I used to paint a lot and I got really into cooking over the pandemic, now Im trying to learn how to sew.

3. Im not a good critic because I like most things so I have a hard time choosing my favourite anything, but my top 3 played songs on spotify are Tezeta, Paper Bag and Zina

4. I have a twin (fraternal), she just got married over the summer and we got to have the wedding in Morocco with all our family.

5. I was named most likely to become a motivational speaker in my senior yearbook which has (thankfully) proven to be totally inaccurate so far.
